track_notes: This tract is good for W7W/WE-017 & W7W/WE-018. Inland Empire Paper owns this ground and they require you get an access permit, which is good for all of there property here is the link http://iepco.com/forestry/rec-use/ a good read on all they rules, Hiking, Horses, ATV & motorcycles. Blanchard Hump, parking Area is about 10 miles East of Spirit Lake Idaho on the Blanchard Cutoff road.  WE-017 is less then a 4 mile round trip if you plan to do both WE-017 & WE-018 I would use a motorcycle or ATV for the dual activation.  The one thing about IEP ground is they have roads going every where most lead to a dead end, the tracts eliminate all this confusion.
